top_values: {"1985,\"An Early Frost\",\"NBC\",\"Michael Pierson\",\"Aidan Quinn\",\"The first made-for-television film to address people with AIDS.\"": 1, "1986,\"St. Elsewhere\",\"NBC\",\"Dr. Robert Caldwell\",\"Mark Harmon\",\"In \\\"Family Feud\\\" aired Jan. 29, 1986, Dr. Caldwell was diagnosed with HIV after leaving the hospital his former colleagues are informed of his death in season six.\"": 1, "1994-,\"General Hospital\",\"ABC\",\"Robin Scorpio\",\"Kimberly McCullough\",\"white female teenager, infected by her boyfriend Stone Cates.\"": 1, "1996,\"Murder One\",\"ABC\",\"Richard Cross\",\"Stanley Tucci\",\"Cross is an unscrupulous businessman whose imminent death from AIDS leads to an ethical awakening.\"": 1, "1997,\"Oz\",\"HBO\",\"Various including Antonio Nappa, James Robson, Nat Ginzburg and Clarence Seroy\",\"Various\",\"Men, infected while in prison, HIV positive inmates are isolated in Unit E, a cell block exclusively for HIV positive inmates not allowed to be amongst general inmate population.\"": 1}
